The symptoms and findings of the swelling over the maxilla, hearing loss, and elevated parathyroid hormone concentration suggest the most likely diagnosis is a parathyroid hormone-related protein (PTHrP)-secreting tumor, which can cause hypercalcemia and bone resorption. Increased activity of nuclear factor-κB is associated with PTHrP secretion in tumors. Defective synthesis of dynein is associated with primary ciliary dyskinesia. Defective synthesis of type I collagen is associated with osteogenesis imperfecta. Decreased activity of carbonic anhydrase II is associated with osteopetrosis.
